enter Stadium in Glen Allen  the Cobb Village 12 in Leesburg  and the Cobb Cine Bistro at Peninsula Town Center and AMC Hampton 24 in Hampton  The movie will also be seen in major cities across the nation  including Atlanta  Ga  Houston  Texas  and Burbank  Calif  The movie follows a group of cadets through wartime life in barracks and depicts their actions leading up to and during the Battle of New Market  in which the Corps of Cadets played a pivotal role and as a result of which 10 cadets died  The Institute s historic grounds were used throughout the film  with current cadets and recent graduates taking part in the production  Its release falls in the year of the 150th anniversary of the battle  and the film features scenes from the 2013 observance of VMI s annual New Market parade and ceremony  Outside of Virginia  the film will be playing at the following theaters  Addison  Ill    Marcus Addison Cinema Alpharetta  Ga    AMC Mansell Crossing 14 Atlanta  Ga    Cobb Cine Bistro at Town Brookhaven Burbank  Calif    AMC Burbank 8 Canton  Mich    Emagine Theatres Canton Chicago Heights  Ill    Marcus Chicago Heights Cinema Columbia  S C    AMC Dutch Square Mall 14 Columbus  Ohio   Marcus Crosswoods Cinema Elk River  Minn    Marcus Elk River Cinema Houston  Texas   Regal Houston Marq E Stadium 23  AMC Gulf Point 30  AMC Willowbrook 24  and AMC Studio 30 IMAX Jacksonville  Fla    Regal Avenues Stadium 20 Novi  Mich    Emagine Theatres Novi Pickerington  Ohio   Marcus Pickerington Theatre Rochester Hills  Mich    Emagine Theatres Rochester Hills Royal Oak  Mich    Emagine Theatres Royal Oak South Barrington  Ill    AMC South Barrington 30  VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 